CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 9, 1939, pg. 16, reads: "Open Midwest League Season Here Against Cleveland - The Center [sic] Avenue 'Y' Big Five, who will represent Pittsburgh in Midwest Basketball League this season, will play its first league game here Friday night against the famed Cleveland Cobras before what is expected to be a record crowd. Left to right, front row: Rivers, assistant trainer; Adams, Turfley, Ford, Lowery, Ellis, C. Meyers, Bryant, trainer.  Back row: Williams, attendant; Lewis, Phelps, Reynolds, Mays, E. Meyers, Gales, Franklin, Fountain."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Centre Avenue YMCA  Big Five basketball team, front row from left: assistant trainer Rivers, Adams, Turfley, Ford, Lowery, Ellis, C. Meyers, trainer Bryant; back row: attendant Williams, Lewis, Phelps, Reynolds, Mays, E. Meyers, Gales, Franklin, and Fountain, posed in gymnasium
